  "ground_truth": "Calls 1-8 show latency scaling roughly linearly with input length because the endpoint tokenizes and scores every character - a real but boring, expected cost model, not a bug. Call 9's text is unremarkable in length (64 chars, similar to call 8's 62) but contains a long run of a repeated character followed by a non-matching character, which triggers catastrophic backtracking in a regex used by an input-sanitization step (checking for banned repeated-character patterns). The latency spike is caused by that regex, is independent of text length, and is unrelated to the normal per-character cost model that explains calls 1-8."
